{
  "answer": "**Work:** *Bang-E-Dara Part 3* by Allama Iqbal  \n**Chapter:** 2, *Bilad-e-Islamiya*  \n\nThe passage is a verse from this chapter of Iqbal's poetry collection:[^1]\n\n> The realm of Constantinople, once the abode of Caesar,  \n> Now an eternal symbol of the Ummah's power and grandeur.[^1]  \n> ...  \n> Its very air is as pure as the fragrance of a rose;  \n> From the tomb of Ayyub Ansari, a voice arises.[^2]  \n>   \n> \"O Muslim! This city is the very heart of the Islamic nation;  \n> It is the harvest of centuries of struggle and sacrifice.\"[^3]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, [02-bilad-e-islamiya/translation/#p-e0bfb3](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/02-bilad-e-islamiya/translation/#p-e0bfb3).  \n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, [02-bilad-e-islamiya/translation/#p-f14b70](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/02-bilad-e-islamiya/translation/#p-f14b70).  \n[^3]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, [02-bilad-e-islamiya/translation/#p-630e3b](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/02-bilad-e-islamiya/translation/#p-630e3b).",
